<br>
The day after the ten day period allowed for the accused to come forward, a trial will commence inside the House of Justice forum. The Chief Judge will ask both sides to issue him a witness list (WL). The witness list will contain a list of every witness the defense and prosecution will call forward during the trial. If someone is found during a trial who does not appear on the witness list, he must be approved by the Chief Judge on record before being called forward. The accused may not be forced or coerced into being a witness. The Trial will then commence by an opening statement by the Chief Judge pertaining to the case.<br>
<br>
The Chief Judge will then ask the prosecution to please call his first witness. The threads that follow will be one question from the prosecution, and one answer from the witness. This prosecution will have until 12:00 AM EST that night to finish asking questions. <br>
<br>
The following day the Chief Judge will give the floor to the defense and allow him to cross examine the witness if he so desires until 12:00 AM EST. It will take place as before with the prosecution asking a single quesiton in a thread, and the witness answering.<br>
<br>
This format will be used through out the case. Whomever the Judge gives the floor may call a witness of their choice and question them for one day. If the Chief Judge ever believe a witness is not cooperating by responding in a fair ammount of time, he may extend the questioning period until he believes the witness is cooperating. If a witness does not cooperate the Chief Judge may order them to one to ten days in elfcatraz.<br>
<br>
The Chief judge must be sure to be fair allowing both sides to call all their witnesses given to the Chief Judge prior to the case, and to allow each party to cross examine the other witness. If both parties have the same individual as a witness on the WL, that witness will be asked questions by both parties, and cross examined by both parties accordingly.<br>
<br>
If any post is made that disrupts trial decorum, the Chief Judge has the obligation to take a screen shot, and edit or delete the post from the Trial thread record.<br>
<br>
The jury will be given three days to review the trial, and the trial thread. If the jury is unable to come to a decision in three days they jury will be given another three days to come to a decision. If at this time it is not able to come to a decision, it will declare itself deadlocke, and the trial will have to be run again. The results will be determined by a majority, not an absolute agreement among jurors.<br>
<br>
If the accused would prefer a Chief Judge run trial instead of a jury trial the Chief Judge will be given up to seven days to come to a decision, he may issue a decision at anytime before that.<br>
<br>
